## LogGuard Terminal Compression

Always prefix execution commands with `uv run lg run` (default: exec mode, no shell quoting loss).

### Default (exec mode — safe, quoting preserved)

```bash
uv run lg run python script.py
uv run lg run python -c "import fastapi, bleach; print('ok')"
uv run lg run -- pytest tests/ -k "not slow"
uv run lg run -- uv run python -c "print(1)"
```

Use `--` before commands that have their own flags (POSIX convention).

### Shell mode (opt-in — pipes, &&, redirects)

```bash
uv run lg run --shell "cat file.log | grep ERROR | head"
uv run lg run --shell "echo first && echo second"
```

Do **not** use `--shell` for normal commands; default exec mode handles spaces and quotes correctly.

### Other commands

- `uv run lg read <file_path>`: Compress a log file.
- `uv run lg raw <id>`: Full uncompressed output by run ID.
- `uv run lg get <id> <n> [<m> ...]`: Print specific `[#n]` extracted values.
- `uv run lg history [-n N]`: Recent runs with compression metrics.

If a compressed summary hides critical details, retrieve the full output using `uv run lg raw <id>` where `<id>` is shown in the `[LogGuard:<id>]` header.
